page.title: 14THE KINGS HEAD IN KEELBY
page.content: The Kings Head is a pub which has been standing since 1850.Henry Coulding has owned the pub for 9 years.The oldest part of the pub is the front.It has a full pub licence which means it can sell all drinks.Friday,Saturday and Sunday are the busiest days.On those days about 130 people are in the pub.It has two rooms.A lounge and a bar.The pub gets mostly village people from Monday to Thursday.At the weekend strangers come at 7.30pm till 9.00pm limit.The pub has got about 400 glasses and the most popular spirit is Bells Scotch whiskey and lager is also popular there.Working in the pub are two bar maids and four helpers.
